Description: AAVA 2.0 represents a significant structural evolution from AAVA 1.0 with major schema reorganization, agent renaming, and field restructuring. The migration introduces breaking changes that require careful orchestration.
Core semantic meaning is preserved across all three agents, but structural presentation has been completely reorganized with new container hierarchies and field naming conventions.
Complete structural reorganization from flat node array to hierarchical workFlowDetail/workflowAgents structure. All field names have been systematically updated.
Schema evolution represents a major version change with breaking compatibility. Migration tooling will be required for all downstream systems.
High semantic preservation despite structural changes. All core agent functionality and descriptions remain intact.
Low structural similarity due to complete schema reorganization and field renaming across all levels.
AAVA 1.0 demonstrates perfect JSON syntax correctness with valid structure and no orphaned references.
AAVA 2.0 demonstrates perfect JSON syntax correctness with valid hierarchical structure and consistent field naming.
Both versions maintain perfect syntactic and structural correctness.
Good overall alignment with high semantic preservation offset by significant structural changes requiring migration effort.
No syntax errors detected. Valid JSON structure with consistent field naming and proper array/object nesting.
No syntax errors detected. Valid JSON structure with improved hierarchical organization and consistent naming conventions.
